Hospitals are becoming mortuaries instead of sanctuaries. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Police will now guard 24-hour community healthcare facilities in Gauteng. The provincial health department wants to ensure that patients and staff are safe following recent attacks at facilities. READ: JMPD to escort medics to crime hotspots In one attack, young men assaulted another man at the South Rand Hospital. A video of the attack was shared on social media. READ: SAMA: Rising attacks on healthcare workers a concern The health department said it will introduce measures such as CCTV and panic buttons linked to police stations. They will also engage unions to find long-term solutions.